## Session 1 — Python App (Initial Release)

### Core architecture
- Three-layer design: browser GUI → HTTP API server → bootloader backend
- `IBootBackend` abstract interface with `(ok, value)` result tuple pattern
- `PlatformDetector` — detects OS and active bootloader at startup, auto-selects backend
- `Backup` utility — timestamped config copies saved before every write operation
- `Logger` utility — append-only timestamped operation log (`blm.log`)
- `MockBackend` — full in-memory demo backend with 7 realistic boot entries
- Undo stack — every write operation pushes a precise reversal lambda (up to 10 deep)
- Settings persistence — preferences saved to `settings.json`, restored on every launch

### GRUB2 backend
- Parses `/boot/grub/grub.cfg` and `/boot/grub2/grub.cfg` (Fedora/RHEL)
- `set_default` — writes `GRUB_DEFAULT`, runs `grub-mkconfig` or `grub2-mkconfig`
- `delete_entry` — removes BLM-managed snippets; explains why auto-generated entries cannot be deleted
- Guards against deletion of the current default entry

### systemd-boot backend
- Scans `/boot/loader/entries/*.conf`
- `set_default` — rewrites `default=` line with backup
- `delete_entry` — removes `.conf` file with backup
- `rename_entry` — edits `title=` line in place with backup and undo

### Windows BCD backend
- `list_entries` — parses `bcdedit /enum ALL /v` output; reads display order from Boot Manager block
- Handles Windows Boot Loader, Windows Boot Sector, Resume from Hibernate
- `set_default`, `delete_entry`, `rename_entry`, `move_entry` — all via bcdedit with undo
- UAC elevation detection with clear human-readable error

### macOS backend
- Apple Silicon detection at init; read-only on Apple Silicon
- Intel: `bless --setBoot` (partial implementation)

### HTTP API server
- All endpoints bound to `127.0.0.1` — never network-accessible
- Full endpoint list: `/api/info`, `/api/entries`, `/api/log`, `/api/undo-info`,
  `/api/settings`, `/api/ready`, `/api/set-default`, `/api/delete`, `/api/rename`,
  `/api/move`, `/api/rescan`, `/api/undo`, `/api/quit`
- `winUpdatePending` detection via Windows registry `RebootRequired` key
- Port conflict handling — tries 7373–7382
- `SIGINT` / `SIGBREAK` signal handling for clean Ctrl+C on Windows and Linux

### Browser GUI
- Four tabs: Boot Entries, Platform Support, Settings, Log
- Color-coded entry tags; green left border on default entry
- Full entry detail panel; dark mode; XSS protection; toast notifications

### Bug fixes (Session 1 — 18 fixes)

| # | Problem | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Checkbox could not be unchecked after first click | Toggle-deselect + `stopPropagation` on checkbox |
| 2 | Windows BCD returned empty list silently when not elevated | Clear error message with step-by-step instructions |
| 3 | Disclaimer shown once ever — never appeared again | Added Settings toggle to re-enable or permanently disable |
| 4 | Boot list not refreshed on launch — manual rescan required | Backend pre-scans on startup; GUI polls `/api/ready` before loading |
| 5 | Ctrl+C did not cleanly stop the server on Windows | `signal.SIGINT` + `SIGBREAK` handlers with `finally` block |
| 6 | BCD `move_entry` returned "not yet implemented" | Implemented via `bcdedit /displayorder` with full reordered GUID list |
| 7 | BCD parser missed display order and some entry types | Reads `displayorder` from Boot Manager block; handles Boot Sector and Hibernate |
| 8 | No way to undo a change | Full undo stack — every write pushes a precise undo lambda; GUI button label shows what will be undone |
| 9 | No warning when Windows Update reboot was pending | Registry check; amber warning banner shown at top of app |
| 10 | Browser tab title never changed | Updates to show selected entry name; resets on deselect |
| 11 | Stale detail panel shown after rescan removed selected entry | Rescan deselects cleanly if entry no longer exists |
| 12 | Status line showed stale count after Apply | Status driven by real undo stack state, not a click counter |
| 13 | Hard crash if port 7373 was in use | Tries ports 7373–7382; prints which port was bound |
| 14 | No confirmation dialog before changing the default boot entry | Confirmation dialog added; controlled by same toggle as delete |
| 15 | Settings reset to defaults on every restart | Persisted to `settings.json`; loaded on every launch with corrupt-file fallback |
| 16 | BCD delete/rename had no undo support | `rename_entry` pushes proper undo; `delete_entry` pushes honest irreversible explanation |
| 17 | Mock backend delete/rename had no undo | Both push precise undo lambdas — full undo coverage in demo mode |
| 18 | Pending change count was a cosmetic click counter | Replaced with `_hasChanges` driven by real undo stack via `/api/undo-info` |

