## Session 4 — Classic OpenGL 2.1 Renderer Variant

Added `blm-gui-classic` build target using `imgui_impl_opengl2` instead of
`imgui_impl_opengl3`. Runs on old integrated GPUs, VMs (VirtualBox, QEMU,
old VMware), and systems with GL 2.1 only. Identical features to the modern variant —
only the renderer backend differs.

**Build:** `./build.sh --classic` (or `build.bat --classic`)

### Bug fixes (Session 4)

| # | Problem | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 32 | `IMGUI_IMPL_OPENGL_LOADER_CUSTOM` disabled ImGui's bundled GL loader — hundreds of undefined symbols | Removed the define; `imgui_impl_opengl3_loader.h` is self-sufficient |
| 33 | No way to run the GUI on hardware that does not support OpenGL 3.3 | Added `blm-gui-classic` target using `imgui_impl_opengl2` |
| 34 | `GLFW_OPENGL_FORWARD_COMPAT` hint included unconditionally — invalid under GL 2.1 | Moved inside `#ifndef BLM_CLASSIC` block |

