## Session 10 — Full Audit and Verification

All 6 previously-identified open bugs confirmed fixed in prior sessions.
All 4 C++ targets rebuilt from scratch: zero errors, zero warnings.
123/123 tests passing.

---

## Session 11 — systemd-boot `move_entry`, GRUB2 Error Message

**systemd-boot `move_entry` implemented.** Reorders entries by renaming `.conf` files
with numeric prefixes (`10_stem.conf`, `20_stem.conf`, …). Two-phase rename via
`.blm_tmp` intermediates avoids collisions when swapping adjacent entries.
Full undo lambda restores all filenames and the default. All boundary conditions
handled with clear error messages.

**GRUB2 `move_entry` error message improved.** Now explains specifically why
auto-generated entries cannot be reordered, names the target entry, recommends
`Set Default` as the correct tool, and mentions `GRUB_DEFAULT=<index>` as an alternative.

---

## Session 12 — Windows SDL2 Without vcpkg: `build_novcpkg.bat`

vcpkg raised "No access" even running as Administrator due to antivirus/ACL restrictions.

`gui-nuklear/build_novcpkg.bat` — now the recommended Windows build path. No admin
rights required. Downloads `SDL2-devel-2.32.0-VC.zip` (~6 MB) from GitHub releases
using PowerShell's `Invoke-WebRequest`; falls back to `%USERPROFILE%\SDL2` if
`C:\SDL2` is not writable. Builds both `blm-backend.exe` and `blm-gui-nuklear.exe`.

---

## Session 13 — pygame Nuklear-style GUI (New Default)

Native-window GUI for the Python app using **pygame**. Becomes the new default
GUI mode (`--browser` uses the old browser GUI).

Mirrors all browser GUI features: four tabs, entry list with color-coded tags,
detail panel, all actions, confirm dialogs, demo mode banner, dark theme, toast
notifications, settings persistence.

