## Session 27 — Buttons Greyed Out + Settings Tab Incomplete

### Bug 65 — Up/Down/Rename buttons greyed out due to writable race condition

**File:** `gui-nuklear/src/main.cpp`

`doRefresh()` fires `listEntries` and `backendInfo` simultaneously. `listEntries`
responds first — the user sees entries and immediately tries to click Up/Down/Rename
— but `backendInfo` has not yet fired, so `app.writable` is still `false`.
All buttons requiring `canWrite` are greyed.

**Fix:** When `listEntries` succeeds and entries are non-empty, immediately set
`app.writable = true`. The `backendInfo` callback confirms or corrects the value
when it arrives.

### Settings tab — fully populated

Added four sections matching the Python version:
- **Behaviour** — confirm dialogs checkbox (wired)
- **Mode** — live vs demo indicator, privilege status
- **File paths** — log file path, backups path (platform-aware)
- **Backend** — backend name and kind from `backendInfo` callback

---

## Session 28 — Unicode Rendering Fix, Detail Panel Polish

### Bug 66 — Unicode symbols render as `?` on Windows

Nuklear's built-in bitmap font covers ASCII 32–127 only. Characters outside
that range (★, ⚠, 🔒) render as `?`.

**Fix:** Replaced all Unicode symbols in Nuklear-rendered strings with ASCII equivalents:

| Was | Now |
|---|---|
| `★` (default marker in list) | `[default]` |
| `⚠` (read-only label) | `[read-only]` |
| `★  Current default boot entry` | `Default boot entry` |
| `⚠  Read-only` | `Read-only — cannot be modified` |

### Detail panel improvements
- Horizontal rule between name and field rows
- Label column widened from 90px to 100px
- Status badges in their own section below a separator; hidden when none apply
- Field row height increased from 18px to 20px

